bridgeTransferFrom(address,address,addre.details: Callback for `IERC20Bridge`. Deposits or withdraws tokens from a dydx account.      Notes:         1. This bridge must be set as an operator of the input dydx account.         2. This function may only be called in the context of the 0x Exchange.         3. The maker or taker of the 0x order must be the dydx account owner.         4. Deposits into dydx are made from the `from` address.         5. Withdrawals from dydx are made to the `to` address.         6. Calling this function must always withdraw at least `amount`,            otherwise the `ERC20Bridge` will revert.

params.amount: Minimum amount of `toTokenAddress` tokens to deposit or withdraw.
params.from: The sender of the tokens and owner of the dydx account.

bridgeTransferFrom(address,address,addre.return: success The magic bytes if successful.
